parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or even catch fire, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Burning smell coming from under the dash
battery drain
vehicle stalling
vehicle catching fire from the ignition area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer light can make it difficult or impossible to read the vehicle's speed, increasing the risk of accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: Speedometer light is out
unable to read speed during the day or night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Bracket Rust and Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and failure of the fuel tank bracket can cause the fuel tank to drop while the vehicle is in motion, potentially leading to a fuel leak, fire, or explosion, which can result in serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: The fuel tank bracket shows signs of rust
the fuel tank drops while the vehicle is in motion
the fuel tank is dragged behind the vehicle
a hole is ripped in the gas tank
sparks are generated
and there is a risk of fire or explosion.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Buckle Release Button Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle release button can prevent the proper use of the seat belt, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle release button breaks
the buckle does not release
the male portion of the buckle does not stay latched into the female portion
the seat belt does not clasp.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can lead to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of braking power
brakes failing to engage
brake pads or rotors worn down excessively
brakes grinding or making unusual noises
brake warning lights illuminating on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of rear brake components can cause the brakes to fail, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rear brake shoes or pads falling off
rear brake drums or rotors excessively worn
rear brake failure
unusual noises or vibrations from the rear brakes.
